    "Specifically, the accuracy for D IDK remains 61.8 for both EARLY_STOP and CONVERGENCE, with a small decrease on the number of willingly answered questions (58.7 → 55.6).",
    "Practical Implications.",
    "This work highlights the risk in using supervised fine-tuning to update LLMs' knowledge, as we present empirical evidence that acquiring new knowledge through fine-tuning is correlated with hallucinations w.r.t pre-existing knowledge.",
    "Additionally, this work raises important questions for future exploration regarding fine-tuning practices.",
    "We saw that Unknown examples are fitted slower than the Known ones, thus their negative effect manifests as a form of overfitting, which emphasizes the importance of using early-stopping instead of a fixed number of fine-tuning steps."
